  "text": "Validates canonical payloads between workflow steps so schema drift, missing fields, enum changes, and connector-specific shape changes are caught before they break downstream automations. Trigger: Webhook / Sub-workflow | Output: Contract validation report + quarantine decision How it works: [{\"step\":1,\"name\":\"Receive Payload Batch\",\"description\":\"Captures payloads emitted by upstream workflow steps before they are passed to downstream automations.\",\"type\":\"trigger\",\"color\":\"green\"},{\"step\":2,\"name\":\"Load Expected Contract\",\"description\":\"Looks up the required schema version, required fields, enums, and routing metadata for the named workflow step.\",\"type\":\"data\",\"color\":\"blue\"},{\"step\":3,\"name\":\"Validate Payload Shape\",\"description\":\"Checks required fields, types, arrays, timestamps, and nested objects against the canonical contract.\",\"type\":\"data\",\"color\":\"blue\"},{\"step\":4,\"name\":\"AI Drift Analysis\",\"description\":\"AI Agent explains whether the failure was likely caused by a connector change, naming drift, or an upstream workflow regression.\",\"type\":\"ai\",\"color\":\"purple\"},{\"step\":5,\"name\":\"Pass or Quarantine\",\"description\":\"Routes valid payloads forward and sends invalid ones to a quarantine sink with validation context attached.\",\"type\":\"output\",\"color\":\"orange\"}] Platforms: n8n, recipe-card, n8n-starter, workato, zapier, claude-workflow, openai-workflow",
